===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|desert||}}

# To [[leave]] (a [[military]] or [[naval]] [[unit]]) without [[permission]] with the [[intent]] to [[permanently]] [[absent]] [[oneself]] from its [[control]] or [[administration]].
# To leave ([[anything]] that [[depend]]s on one's [[presence]] to [[survive]], [[exist]], or [[succeed]]), especially when contrary to a [[promise]] or [[obligation]]; to [[abandon]]; to [[forsake]].
#:''You can't just drive off and '''desert''' me here, in the middle of nowhere.''

===Pronunciation===
*dĭzû(r)t', /dɪˈzɜː(r)t/, /<tt>dI"z3:(r)t</tt>/
*{{audio|en-us-desert-verb.ogg|Audio (US), verb}}

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[deserere]]'' "to abandon", formed from ''[[de-]]'' + ''[[serere]]'' "to bind together"

