===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A largely [[barren]] area of land or [[desolate]] [[terrain]] which receives little or no [[precipitation]] over an extended period of time, and which typically has [[sparse]] or no [[vegetation]]; a [[wasteland]].
# A place which lacks some desirable [[quality]] or [[characteristic]]
#:''This town is an intellectual '''desert'''.''
# ''(modifier)'' of, like, or relating to a desert; desolate, [[infertile]]

===Pronunciation===
*dĕ'zə(r)t, /ˈdɛzə(r)t/, /<tt>"dEz@(r)t</tt>/
*{{audio|en-us-desert-noun.ogg|Audio (US), noun}}

===Etymology===
From Ancient Egyptian ''deshret'' "(the) Red Land", formed from ''desher'' "red"

